      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Continuum elastoplastic model with isotropic hardening appropriate for Ti-6Al-4V under quasi-static bending; justified by prior literature and material characterization data.",
      "rationale": "Bilinear isotropic hardening plasticity is well-established for Ti-6Al-4V implant components under quasi-static loading. The model form is consistent with FDA-recognized simulation practices for spinal implants and validated against published coupon test data. Gradation 3 is appropriate and achieved."
