      "rationale": "Eleven non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs from production lots were distributed across two laboratories (n=6 Lab A, n=5 Lab B). Inter-laboratory coefficient of variation for construct stiffness was 4.2%, within acceptable bounds. Sample size supports statistical comparison per ASME V&V 40 guidance. Gradation 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions replicate ASTM F1717 protocol; multiple loading rates or physiologic conditions would achieve Gradation 3.",
      "rationale": "Testing was conducted strictly per ASTM F1717 at a single quasi-static loading rate (5 mm/min). While this is the regulatory standard condition, only a single test condition was employed, precluding assessment of loading-rate sensitivity. Gradation 2 achieved; Gradation 3 required. This is a known gap accepted by the credibility assessment team given the regulatory context of F1717."
    },
